data.value:
Munich, home to approximately 1.5 million people, is known as the capital of the Bavarian state. The BMW Museum, the Munich Residenz, the Frauenkirche and Nymphenburg Palace, Theatinerkirche and the English Garden represent the main attractions of the city.
The city, which is worth seeing with its old squares and churches, has reflected its original fame with the Oktoberfest beer festival. The festival, organized at the beginning of October, attracts millions of people every year.
Marienplatz Street, which is crowded around the clock, has been the main square of the city since 1158. St. Mariensaule. The Church of St. Peter and the Neues Rathaus are among the other buildings you can come across in the region.
